      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden, ¶ 24 November 1863. ¶ Esteemed Professor, ¶  ¶ I take the liberty of sending you the second bill of exchange of £10.- .- ¶  ¶ by this morning's mail as my own further contrib...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">63.11.24a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 20. Jan. 1864. | A. 27 April —' [Received 20 January 1864. Answered 27 April]. Reply letter in this edition as 64-04-27a.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>For a published version of this letter,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see Voigt (1996),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pp. 49-50.</p>
               </note>Melbourne im bot. Garten</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">am 24 Nov.1863</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochverehrter Herr Professor!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit der Morgenpost erlaube ich mir diesmal Ihnen die Secunda eines Wechsels von £10.- .-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>zuzusenden als meinen eignen weitern Beitrag zum nordafrikanischen Reisefond. Die Prima sandte ich Ihnen im letzten Monat. Seit ich die Ehre hatte Ihnen die letzte Abrechnung vorzulegen, sind keine weitern Beiträge für diese Forschungen bei mir eingelaufen; indessen wird unfraglich im Verlauf dieser interessanten u menschenfreundlichen Forschungen noch mancher Landsmann hier sein thätiges Interesse an den Unternehmungen bekunden. Das Schiff Johannes, welches mir durch Herrn Dr Sonders Vermittlung Ihre schöne Sendung bringt ist endlich vor 3 Tagen angelangt. Ich werde aber vor dem Abgang dieser Post nicht in den Besitz Ihrer Gaben gelangen u kann daher erst später über die Vertheilung berichten.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit inniger Hochachtung bleibe ich, verehrter Herr Doctor,der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Durfte<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ich Sie um Ihre photographirte Visitenkarte bitten für meine Sammlung der Bildnisse grosser u befreundeter Zeitgenossen?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24 November 1863.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Esteemed Professor,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I take the liberty of sending you the second bill of exchange of £10.- .-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by this morning's mail as my own further contribution to the North African expedition fund.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The 'Heuglin<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Fund' instituted by Petermann to finance the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>German expedition he had organized to search for the missing<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>German explorer Eduard<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Vogel and to explore unknown parts of Central Africa. M had<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>previously<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>collected contributions from the German community in Australia, as well as contributing personally.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I sent the first copy<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>last month.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Petermann, 25 October 1863<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 63-10-25a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>No further contributions<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for these explorations<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have been received by me, since I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>had the honour of presenting<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the last statement of account to you;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. Petermann, 23 February 1862<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 62-02-23a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>however, in the course of these interesting and philanthropic explorations many a compatriot here will no doubt still want to show<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>lively<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>interest<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the undertaking. The ship<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Johannes</seg>, which brings me your splendid consignment through the agency of Dr Sonder, has finally arrived here three days ago. I shall not be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>able to take possession of your gifts before the departure of this letter, so I cannot report on their distribution<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See A. Petermann to M, 16 May 1863.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>until later.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With cordial respect I remain, esteemed Doctor, your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">May I ask you for your photographic carte-de-visite for my collection of portraits of great contemporaries, who are my friends?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A similar request was made in M to A. Petermann, 25 October 1863 (in this edition as 63-10-25a), and reported as received in M to A. Petermann, 25 July 1864 (in this edition as 64-07-25a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>No image of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Petermann<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been identified at MEL, but see M to J. Haast, 29 July 1862 (in this edition as 62-07-29b) and notes thereto.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
